  "text": "The oil sludge much biodegradation studies utilizing cells from potential material degrada-tion such as mangroves, algae, jellyfish, and the material at the site of the oil sludge contami-nation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , but it can only touch on certain areas, such as the material of mangrove generally found in coastal areas, algae live in shallow ocean surface area, and the material isolated from the location of hydrocarbon contamination [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
